{{Quote|What&mdash;what is this place?''"<br />"''Doctor ''Demagol's'' waiting room. No appointments necessary.|Jarael and imprisoned Jedi Knight [[Ferroh]]|<ref name="kotor8" />}}
'''Flashpoint Stellar Research Station''' was a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Scientist/Legends|scientific]] research station on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Flashpoint (planet)|Flashpoint]] that was [[Battle of Flashpoint Station|captured]] by the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] warrior clans in [[3964 BBY]]. Originally intended for the study of [[Star/Legends|stars]] and related phenomena, Flashpoint Station was located inside a powerful [[Magnetic field/Legends|magnetic shield]]&mdash;the planet Flashpoint was located extremely close to its [[Flashpoint (star)|star]], and organic life usually could not survive on the world's barren surface. In the beginning stages of the [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders]]' [[Mandalorian Wars|war]] with the Republic, Flashpoint Station was taken by the marauders and turned into the operating base for the notorious Mandalorian [[Biologist/Legends|biologist]] [[Demagol]]. From Flashpoint Station, Demagol furthered research into the source of the [[Force power/Legends|powers]] of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]], conducting brutal live experiments on [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] captured near the front lines.

Demagol's collection grew to include a number of Jedi [[Revanchist|crusaders]] [[Ambush on Suurja|captured]] on [[Suurja]], led by the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Darth Malak|Alek]]. After the Mandalorians mistakenly captured and brought to Flashpoint a non-Jedi named [[Jarael]], the [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|Arkanian Offshoot's]] friends, including fugitive former Jedi [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Zayne Carrick]] and escaped Mandalorian warrior [[Rohlan Dyre]], formulated a plan to rescue her. With Carrick posing as a Jedi whom Dyre had captured, they were able to incapacitate Demagol and simulate a fake Republic attack to clear the other Mandalorians off the station. The captive Jedi were freed, although Demagol escaped Republic custody by knocking out Dyre and switching [[Armor/Legends|armor]] with him. After the ordeal was over, the Jedi destroyed Flashpoint Station.

==Description==
{{Quote|Station's on a planet ridiculously close to its star. The day's just an hour long&mdash;and anyone who sets foot outside the magnetic field goes 'poof!' from the heat and radiation.|Marn Hierogryph|<ref name="kotor8" />}}
[[File:FlashpointPlanet-KOTOR10.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The barren world of Flashpoint]]
Located on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Flashpoint (planet)|Flashpoint]], the Flashpoint Stellar Research Station was a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Scientist/Legends|scientific]] outpost established to study the life and [[Death/Legends|death]] of [[Star/Legends|stars]] and other solar phenomena.<ref name="cswe" /> Flashpoint Station was located on a small, [[Desert/Legends|desert]] world with no [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]], as the planet was extremely close to its [[Flashpoint (star)|star]]. The massive amount of heat and [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]] produced by the nearby star necessitated the creation of a powerful [[Magnetic field/Legends|magnetic shield]]&mdash;without it, nothing could survive on the planet's surface<ref name="kotor8" /> during Flashpoint's [[Standard hour/Legends|hour]]-long [[Standard day/Legends|days]]. The [[Magnet/Legends|magnetic]] [[Deflector shield/Legends|shield]] protected a roughly circular area of the planet's surface and was generated by several towers. For a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] to land at Flashpoint Station, the magnetic field had to be lowered, although this was unsafe to do during Flashpoint's brief and dangerous days.<ref name="kotor10">[[Knights of the Old Republic 10|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 10]]</ref> During the Republic's tenure in charge of the station, their scientists employed heavily shielded [[Ministry-class orbital shuttle|''Ministry''-class orbital shuttles]] while carrying out research.<ref name="kotorcg">''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Even with the magnetic field, the planet had no atmosphere, requiring all present at the station to wear airtight [[Environment suit/Legends|suits]] while outside. The station's main structure was a bunker near the center of camp, surrounded by a larger outdoor area that was big enough to hold several starships. The station was equipped with [[Blaster/Legends|guns]] to repel unwanted intruders and a [[Comm unit/Legends|comm system]] to contact nearby starships. The bunker itself was pressurized and featured a large, open entrance room that led into much narrower corridors. Deeper within the compound was a central research room, which the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Doctor/Legends|doctor]] [[Demagol]] made into his office during the Mandalorian occupation amidst their [[Mandalorian Wars|war]] with the Republic. Demagol adorned the room with the [[Bone/Legends|bones]] and skulls of several victims, as well as a number of [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]]; the room itself was covered in [[Blood/Legends|bloodstains]]. The room also featured a vertical board to which Demagol strapped his [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] test subjects and thereupon working on them with his vast array of medical tools.<ref name="kotor10" />

==History==
{{Quote|Since your Jedi scouts started nosing around the frontier, we've got a standing order&mdash;all Jedi are to be taken alive&mdash;to Demagol.|Rohlan Dyre, to Zayne Carrick|<ref name="kotor8" />}}
Flashpoint Station was originally constructed and staffed by the Galactic Republic,<ref name="cswe" /> which defunded a [[Unidentified solar observatory|solar observatory]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Metellos 3]] in order to pay for the station.<ref name="kotor37">[[Knights of the Old Republic 37|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 37]]</ref> In [[3964 BBY]], the [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders]], who had previously carved out their own empire beyond the reaches of the Republic, began to encroach upon Republic [[Realspace/Legends|space]] in the name of the Mandalorian warrior clans. With Flashpoint Station sitting on the edge of Republic territory, the Mandalorians [[Battle of Flashpoint Station|captured]] the facility.<ref name="prime" /> After Flashpoint Station fell into Mandalorian control, they began to use it to their own ends&mdash;the station was given over to Demagol, the top Mandalorian [[Biologist/Legends|biologist]], as a base where he could advance his studies into the [[Force power/Legends|powers]] and abilities of Jedi. As the first Jedi [[Scout/Legends|scouts]] were discovered investigating the frontier, the Mandalorians were ordered to bring all captured Jedi alive<ref name="kotor8" /> to Demagol, who conducted experiments on his living [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]], with many dying under his watch.<ref name="kotor8" /> During the early days of the war, the Mandalorian [[Teroch-type gunship|''Teroch''-type gunship]] was primarily used to ferry prisoners to Flashpoint.<ref name="kotorcg" />

During Demagol's reign on Flashpoint, a number of Jedi attempted to escape their predicament, but all died within [[Standard minute/Legends|minutes]] under Flashpoint's unforgiving sun.<ref name="kotor37" /> As the Mandalorians continued to threaten the Outer Rim, a [[Revanchist|group]] of Jedi, led by the charismatic [[Revan/Legends|Revan]], defied the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council's]] wishes and set out to battle the Mandalorians. However, many of these Jedi, including Revan's right-hand man, [[Darth Malak|Alek]], were [[Ambush on Suurja|captured]] on the war-torn world of [[Suurja]] and brought to Flashpoint Station as a fresh crop for Demagol. The new arrivals were relentlessly [[Torture/Legends|tortured]], especially Alek, who proved willing to subject himself to more suffering in order to protect his fellows. While Demagol busied himself with his test subjects, the Mandalorians ramped up the fight against the Republic, launching a major offensive aimed at taking the valuable world of [[Taris/Legends|Taris]]. In one [[Battle of Vanquo|major battle]] at [[Vanquo]], the Mandalorians mistook the [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|Arkanian Offshoot]] [[Jarael]] as a Jedi&mdash;she had posed as one in a previous caper on the world. She was promptly taken prisoner and brought to Flashpoint Station, where Alek, recognizing that she was not a Jedi, protected her by volunteering himself for "research" in her place.<ref name="kotor8" />

[[File:FlashpointCrew.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Demagol prepares to operate on the captive Zayne Carrick.]]
Unbeknownst to Demagol, Jarael's friends&mdash;including the fugitive former Jedi [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Zayne Carrick]]&mdash;had set out for Flashpoint to rescue her and the other Jedi trapped there. Assisted by escaped Mandalorian warrior [[Rohlan Dyre]], Carrick developed a plan to sabotage Flashpoint Station from the inside&mdash;he would pose as a Jedi whom Dyre had captured on Vanquo and thus gain entry to the heavily guarded station. After landing safely within the magnetic shield, Dyre marched Carrick into Demagol's office and demanded that Demagol get to work on the young Padawan. Demagol acquiesced and brought Carrick to his operating room in the back&mdash;once there, Dyre knocked Demagol unconscious. Dyre locked Demagol in a storage closet, while Carrick put the scientist's [[Armor/Legends|armor]] on and posed as Demagol while proclaiming to the captive Jedi that Carrick had died during an experiment. Not realizing the situation, an enraged Jarael attacked the false Demagol, although she relented after Zayne whispered her name and confused her. "Demagol" and Dyre began the next part of their plan, simulating a Republic attack on the station. Carrick's [[Snivvian/Legends|Snivvian]] friend, [[Marn Hierogryph]], posed as a Republic [[Admiral/Legends|admiral]] and sent a [[Holomessage/Legends|holomessage]] to Flashpoint Station, warning of an imminent attack. Hierogryph's message coincided with the remote detonation of several [[Mining charge/Legends|mining charges]] previously found on Vanquo, which destroyed a number of captured Republic ships around the station, along with almost all of the towers generating the station's magnetic shield.<ref name="kotor10" />

The explosions caused a panic amongst the Mandalorians about the station, and Dyre directed them to flee on a Mandalorian-made [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]]. Dyre also told them to report to [[Mandalore the Ultimate|Mandalore]] of the Republic's new "tactic" of remotely detonating Republic ships captured by the Mandalorians&mdash;a complete lie, invented by Hierogryph. Once all the other Mandalorians had left, Carrick returned to the bunker where the Jedi were being held and revealed himself as the false Demagol, thrilling Jarael and the other prisoners.<ref name="kotor10" /> After their caper, Dyre returned to collect the fallen Demagol. However, the warrior let his guard down, and Demagol injected him with a substance that incapacitated him. Demagol switched armors with Dyre, posing as him after returning to the others, while Dyre, in Demagol's armor, was taken into Republic custody.<ref name="kotor48">[[Knights of the Old Republic 48|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 48]]</ref> The Jedi prisoners and Carrick's group went their separate ways after the incident, using the rest of the [[Mining/Legends|mining]] charges<ref name="kotor10" /> to destroy Flashpoint Station entirely.<ref name="cswe" />

==Inhabitants==
{{Quote|This place is all blaze and no glory. Only drama here is keeping the shield generators going. I'd be half-asleep&mdash;if these hour-long days let me sleep.|A Mandalorian stationed at Flashpoint|<ref name="kotor10" />}}
[[File:Demagol-KotOR48.jpg|thumb|left|150px|The notorious Doctor Demagol]]
Originally inhabited by a team of Republic scientists, by 3964 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]], Flashpoint Station had been totally taken over by the Mandalorians. Flashpoint Station was subsequently staffed by a group of Mandalorian warriors, led by the notorious biologist Demagol.<ref name="kotor8" /> Demagol, real name Antos Wyrick,<ref name="kotor48" /> had previously studied the powers of Jedi for [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]], believing [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], as the Jedi explained it, to be a myth meant to hide the true source of their abilities. On Flashpoint Station, Demagol was assisted by an ambitious Mandalorian named [[Pulsipher]], who disagreed with Demagol that the Force was the result of [[Gene/Legends|genetic]] modifications, instead believing that the Jedi's powers were a result of artifacts and trinkets carried by the Force wielders.<ref name="demagol">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/fiction/demagol/index.html?page=1|text="The Secret Journal of Doctor Demagol"|int=The Secret Journal of Doctor Demagol (article)|newhost=Suvudu}}</ref> The rest of the Mandalorians at the station were mostly employed as guards and assistants, charged with defending the isolated outpost and keeping the magnetic shield running<ref name="kotor10" />&mdash;the majority found it a desolate, wretched place,<ref name="demagol" /> some losing [[Sleep/Legends|sleep]] due to Flashpoint's hour-long days.<ref name="kotor10" />

Mandalorian crews bringing in captive Jedi also visited Flashpoint Station on occasion<ref name="kotor10" />&mdash;the Jedi themselves were kept in the installation's entrance room, which had been outfitted with gurneys and benches. The Jedi on Flashpoint were constantly tortured,<ref name="kotor8" /> many killed by Demagol,<ref name="kotor10" /> with others perishing in futile escape attempts.<ref name="kotor37" /> One Jedi in particular, Alek&mdash;known to Demagol as "Squint"&mdash;proved himself to be exceptionally hardy, withstanding all of Demagol's most painful procedures.<ref name="demagol" /> A well-known leader of the Revanchist movement within the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], Alek took on something of a leadership role amongst the captured Jedi. During Zayne Carrick and Rohlan Dyre's plot to rescue the trapped Jedi, many of the Mandalorians at Flashpoint Station fled,<ref name="kotor10" /> while Demagol escaped in Dyre's armor.<ref name="kotor48" /> The Jedi were freed, detonating their former [[Prison/Legends|prison]] behind them as they left.<ref name="cswe" />

==Behind the scenes==
Flashpoint Stellar Research Station was first mentioned in ''[[The Taris Holofeed: Prime Edition]]'', an [[in-universe]] news report appearing at the end of [[Knights of the Old Republic 0|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 0]], a [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] written by [[John Jackson Miller]] and released in [[2006]].<ref name="prime">{{KOTORbackups|0}}</ref> The station made its first appearance in ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic: Flashpoint]]'', a later story arc of the [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic (comic series)|''Knights of the Old Republic'']] series primarily set at Flashpoint Station.<ref name="kotor8" /><ref name="kotor10" /> The station was later mentioned in a number of ''Knights of the Old Republic'' issues, including two brief flashbacks,<ref name="kotor48" /><ref name="kotor47">[[Knights of the Old Republic 47|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 47]]</ref> as well as several reference books, including ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''<ref name="tea">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> and the ''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''.<ref name="kotorcg" />

